    "created_at": "2016-12-08T21:12:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-12-08T21:12:02Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Actually, I think that can work. If we accept that API guarantees are explicitly or implicitly discarded when there is an error, then we can say that behavior changes when there is an error event don't actually break any API guarantees."
  },
